escription":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Closed","id":"6","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"priority":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/priority/3","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/priorities/major.svg","name":"Major","id":"3"},"issuetype":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issuetype/1","id":"1","description":"A problem which impairs or prevents the functions of the product.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=14803&avatarType=issuetype","name":"Bug","subtask":false,"avatarId":14803}}}},{"id":"28882","self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issueLink/28882","type":{"id":"10103","name":"Relates","inward":"relates to","outward":"relates to","self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issueLinkType/10103"},"outwardIssue":{"id":"28928","key":"EUCA-9132","self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/28928","fields":{"summary":"Instances Ephemeral Storage is not formatted ext3","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Closed","id":"6","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"priority":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/priority/3","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/priorities/major.svg","name":"Major","id":"3"},"issuetype":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issuetype/1","id":"1","description":"A problem which impairs or prevents the functions of the product.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=14803&avatarType=issuetype","name":"Bug","subtask":false,"avatarId":14803}}}}],"assignee":null,"updated":"2015-05-08T17:18:34.404-0500","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Closed","id":"6","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10010","id":"10010","name":"Node Controller"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"*Assessment*\r\n\r\nI was testing this out on the [Group #1 cloud|https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/wiki/display/QA/Euca+4.1+Quality+Dashboard#Euca4.1QualityDashboard-Group#1] using EBS-backed instances that had a block-device-mapping where ephemeral0 was assigned to a particular device.  The metadata information in the EBS-backed instance was correct (per the fix in EUCA-7860), however the ephemeral device was not formatted to ext3.\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nubuntu@euca-10-111-52-182:~$ curl http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/block-device-mapping/; echo\r\nami\r\nemi\r\nephemeral0\r\nroot\r\nubuntu@euca-10-111-52-182:~$ curl http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/block-device-mapping/ephemeral0; echo\r\nsdc\r\nubuntu@euca-10-111-52-182:~$ ls /dev/vd*\r\n/dev/vda  /dev/vda1  /dev/vdb\r\nubuntu@euca-10-111-52-182:~$ sudo parted /dev/vdb print\r\nError: /dev/vdb: unrecognised disk label\r\nubuntu@euca-10-111-52-182:~$ sudo parted /dev/vda1 print\r\nModel: Virtio Block Device (virtblk)\r\nDisk /dev/vda1: 7515MB\r\nSector size (logical/physical): 512B/512B\r\nPartition Table: loop\r\n\r\nNumber  Start  End     Size    File system  Flags\r\n 1      0.00B  7515MB  7515MB  ext4\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n*Steps*\r\n\r\n# Create EBS-backed EMI using existing instance store-backed EMI on [Group #1 cloud|https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/wiki/display/QA/Euca+4.1+Quality+Dashboard#Euca4.1QualityDashboard-Group#1] - ([Ubuntu example can be seen in the KB articles|https://support.eucalyptus.com/hc/en-us/articles/201605884-Creating-an-Ubuntu-EBS-backed-EMI-from-an-Existing-Instance-Store-Backed-Instance])\r\n# Launch an EBS-backed instance from the EBS-backed EMI.  For example:\r\n{code}\r\n# euca-describe-images --region admin-hspencer@group1\r\nIMAGE\temi-1bb60055\t661782123396/ubuntu-trusty-x86_64-ebs-hvm\t661782123396\tavailable\tprivate\tx86_64\tmachine\t\t\t\tebs\thvm\r\nBLOCKDEVICEMAPPING\tEBS\t/dev/sda\tsnap-203ff37f\t7\ttrue\tstandard\r\nIMAGE\temi-8ad9dddb\tubuntu-trusty-20150120/trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1-20150115.img.manifest.xml\t661782123396\tavailable\tprivate\tx86_64\tmachine\t\t\t\tinstance-store\thvm\r\n\r\n# euca-run-instances -k admin-hspencer1 -t m1.large emi-1bb60055 -z two --block-device-mapping=/dev/sdc=ephemeral0 --region admin-hspencer@group1\r\n{code}\r\n# Confirm block device mapping returned in metadata service:\r\n{code}\r\nubuntu@euca-10-111-52-182:~$ curl http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/block-device-mapping/; echo\r\nami\r\nemi\r\nephemeral0\r\nroot\r\nubuntu@euca-10-111-52-182:~$ curl http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/block-device-mapping/ephemeral0; echo\r\nsdc\r\nubuntu@euca-10-111-52-182:~$ ls /dev/vd*\r\n/dev/vda  /dev/vda1  /dev/vdb\r\nubuntu@euca-10-111-52-182:~$ ls /dev/sd*\r\nls: cannot access /dev/sd*: No such file or directory\r\n{code}\r\n# Confirm format of ephemeral storage (should be ext3):\r\n{code}\r\nubuntu@euca-10-111-52-182:~$ sudo parted /dev/vdb print\r\nError: /dev/vdb: unrecognised disk label\r\n{code}","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfie